title: Coaches' Corner: UMD Hockey's Scott Sandelin
text:
Coaches' Corner: UMD Hockey's Scott Sandelin 
By Zach Schneider   12:51 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- The University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) men's hockey team swept a home-and-home series against in-state rival Minnesota this past weekend, and that was a main part of the discussion in this week's "Coaches' Corner" with head coach Scott Sandelin. 
This conversation is part of the weekly show "Bulldog Country," which covers all things UMD and airs every Friday night at 6:30 p.m. on the My 9 Sports Network. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
No. 5 UMD will be on the road this weekend against Notre Dame, with both games set to air in the Northland on the My 9 Sports Network. Friday's game starts at 5:05 p.m., while Saturday's gets underway at 5:35 p.m.
